        "timestamp": "2018-09-06 13:30:53.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\nHello marios,\n\nin your code the progress field is a String in the e2e get Status and Integer for non e2e service.\njust to be sure it's what you wanted to do",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "f793e12ea87786c0addf4d469e42125a9b335263",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1855,
          "name": "Marios Iakovidis",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "marios.iakovidis@huawei.com",
          "username": "MariosIakovidis"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-09-07 08:21:58.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Hello marios,\n > \n > in your code the progress field is a String in the e2e get Status\n > and Integer for non e2e service.\n > just to be sure it's what you wanted to do\n\nHi Romain,\n\nYes that was intended. The thing is, for pollSoRequestStatus, the RequestStatus.getPercentProgress returns int And at pollE2ESoRequestStatus, OperationStatus.getProgress returns String\n\nSo in order to not touch these methods I had to parse int as a string at ServiceOrderItem.setPercentProgress at non-E2E poll\n\nBest,\nMarios",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
